{"parse":{"title":"Board of Theological Education of the Senate of Serampore College","pageid":9650980,"revid":841321232,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\">\n</p>\n<table class=\"infobox vcard\" style=\"width:22em\"><caption class=\"fn org\">Board of Theological Education of the Senate of Serampore College</caption><tbody><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<div class=\"nickname\">BTESSC</div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.65em;\">Type</th><td>\nRegulatory body for <a href=\"/wiki/Theological\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Theological\">Theological</a> education in India</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.65em;\">Established</th><td>\n1975</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.65em;\"><a href=\"/wiki/Chancellor_(education)\" title=\"Chancellor (education)\">Chancellor</a></th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/The_Reverend\" title=\"The Reverend\">The Rev.</a> <a href=\"/wiki/John_Sadananda\" title=\"John Sadananda\">John Sadananda</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Doctor_of_Theology\" title=\"Doctor of Theology\">Dr. Theol.</a> (<a href=\"/wiki/University_of_Gottingen\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"University of Gottingen\">Gottingen</a>)</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.65em;\"><a href=\"/wiki/University_president\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"University president\">President</a></th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/The_Reverend\" title=\"The Reverend\">The Rev.</a> Kavito Zhimo, <a href=\"/wiki/Doctor_of_Theology\" title=\"Doctor of Theology\">D. Th.</a> (<a href=\"/wiki/Senate_of_Serampore_College_(University)\" title=\"Senate of Serampore College (University)\">Serampore</a>)</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.65em;\">Secretary</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/The_Reverend\" title=\"The Reverend\">The Rev.</a> T. Matthews Emmanuel, <a href=\"/wiki/Doctor_of_Theology\" title=\"Doctor of Theology\">D. Th.</a> (<a href=\"/wiki/Senate_of_Serampore_College_(University)\" title=\"Senate of Serampore College (University)\">Serampore</a>)</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.65em;\">Location</th><td class=\"adr\">\n<span class=\"locality\"><a href=\"/wiki/Bangalore\" title=\"Bangalore\">Bangalore</a></span>, <span class=\"state\"><a href=\"/wiki/Karnataka\" title=\"Karnataka\">Karnataka</a></span>, <span class=\"country-name\"><a href=\"/wiki/India\" title=\"India\">India</a></span></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.65em;\">Affiliations</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Senate_of_Serampore_College_(University)\" title=\"Senate of Serampore College (University)\">Senate of Serampore College (University)</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.65em;\">Website</th><td>\n<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external free\" href=\"http://btessc.org\">http://btessc.org</a></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>The Board of Theological Education of the Senate of Serampore College (BTESSC)</b> is the arm of theological education under the <a href=\"/wiki/Senate_of_Serampore_College_(University)\" title=\"Senate of Serampore College (University)\">Senate of Serampore College (University)</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>  BTESSC was formed in 1975.\n</p><p>The <a href=\"/wiki/Senate_of_Serampore_College_(University)\" title=\"Senate of Serampore College (University)\">Senate of Serampore College (University)</a> under which the BTESSC was constituted is a University within the meaning of Section 2 (f)<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> of the <a href=\"/wiki/University_Grants_Commission_(India)\" title=\"University Grants Commission (India)\">University Grants Commission</a> Act, 1956<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> <i>(as modified up to 20 December 1985)</i>.\n</p><p>In fact, Serampore was the first institution<sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> to be given the status of a university in <a href=\"/wiki/India\" title=\"India\">India</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The BTESSC is one of the major representative bodies of churches legally constituted and responsible for administering theological education in South Asia<sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Membership\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Membership</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Its_functions[11]\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Its functions<sup>&#91;11&#93;</sup></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Administration[13]\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Administration<sup>&#91;13&#93;</sup></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#Notable_persons_associated_with_BTESSC\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Notable persons associated with BTESSC</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">6</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Membership\">Membership</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Board_of_Theological_Education_of_the_Senate_of_Serampore_College&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Membership\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The BTESSC is a participating member in the World Conference of Associations of Theological Institutions<sup id=\"cite_ref-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Board_of_Theological_Education_of_the_Senate_of_Serampore_College&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: History\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Serampore was the only means of validating theological training in India until 1978.<sup id=\"cite_ref-9\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup>  The Union Biblical Seminary, Poona was constituted in 1953 as an evangelical theological college at B.Th. and B.D. levels.  It was accredited by the Board of Theological Education of the National Council of Churches in India in 1964 which was formed in 1955 to bring together the unaffiliated Bible schools and seminaries.  UBS was affiliated to Serampore in 1973 at B.D. level.  After a series of joint consultations with Serampore, the Board of Theological Education of NCCI decided in favour of the formation of one national structure for Theological Education in India.  When Serampore accepted the proposal, a joint structure was formed in July 1975 as the <b>Board of Theological Education of the Senate of Serampore College</b>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-10\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span id=\"Its_functions.5B11.5D\"></span><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Its_functions[11]\">Its functions<sup id=\"cite_ref-11\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Board_of_Theological_Education_of_the_Senate_of_Serampore_College&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Its functions[11]\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The functions of the Board as given in the Constitution of the BTESSC (revised and adopted on 3\u20134 February 1994 portray its mandatory role in the promotion of theological education in the country, <i>viz.</i>,\n</p>\n<ul><li>Reflection and pioneering on new methods and style in theological education in relation to the need of the country and of the Churches</li>\n<li>Production of theological literature in general especially in regional languages</li>\n<li>Promotion of the welfare of theological teachers and students</li>\n<li>Development of ecumenical cooperation among theological institutions and their libraries</li>\n<li>Promotion of relationship between Churches, Theological institutions and study centres</li>\n<li>Any other issues related to theological education</li>\n<li>The Board shall recommend names of persons to be considered by the Senate for nomination to be appointed as Senators.</li></ul>\n<p>In matters of theological education, the BTESSC acts as an \"advisory body\" of the <a href=\"/wiki/Senate_of_Serampore_College_(University)\" title=\"Senate of Serampore College (University)\">Senate of Serampore College (University)</a> and the Senate is its voice.<sup id=\"cite_ref-12\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-12\">&#91;12&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span id=\"Administration.5B13.5D\"></span><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Administration[13]\">Administration<sup id=\"cite_ref-13\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-13\">&#91;13&#93;</a></sup></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Board_of_Theological_Education_of_the_Senate_of_Serampore_College&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: Administration[13]\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li>Chairperson - <a href=\"/wiki/The_Reverend\" title=\"The Reverend\">The Rev.</a> Kavito Zhimo, <a href=\"/wiki/Doctor_of_Theology\" title=\"Doctor of Theology\">D. Th.</a> (<a href=\"/wiki/Senate_of_Serampore_College_(University)\" title=\"Senate of Serampore College (University)\">Serampore</a>)</li>\n<li>Secretary \u2013 <a href=\"/wiki/The_Reverend\" title=\"The Reverend\">The Rev.</a> T. Matthews Emmanuel, <a href=\"/wiki/Doctor_of_Theology\" title=\"Doctor of Theology\">D. Th.</a> (<a href=\"/wiki/Senate_of_Serampore_College_(University)\" title=\"Senate of Serampore College (University)\">Serampore</a>)</li>\n<li>Treasurer \u2013 <a href=\"/wiki/Doctor_(title)\" title=\"Doctor (title)\">Dr.</a> Moses Manohar, <a href=\"/wiki/Ph.D.\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Ph.D.\">Ph.D.</a> (<a href=\"/wiki/Madras_University\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Madras University\">Madras</a>),</li>\n<li>Dean for Research of <a href=\"/wiki/SATHRI\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"SATHRI\">SATHRI</a> \u2013 <a href=\"/wiki/The_Reverend\" title=\"The Reverend\">The Rev.</a> <a href=\"/wiki/P._G._George\" title=\"P. G. George\">P. G. George</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Th._D.\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Th. D.\">Th. D.</a>, (<a href=\"/wiki/University_of_Toronto\" title=\"University of Toronto\">Toronto</a>)</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Notable_persons_associated_with_BTESSC\">Notable persons associated with BTESSC</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Board_of_Theological_Education_of_the_Senate_of_Serampore_College&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: Notable persons associated with BTESSC\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/C._L._Furtado\" title=\"C. L. Furtado\">C. L. Furtado</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Church_of_South_India\" title=\"Church of South India\">CSI</a>,</li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/H._S._Wilson\" title=\"H. S. Wilson\">H. S. Wilson</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Church_of_South_India\" title=\"Church of South India\">CSI</a>,</li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Daniel_D._Chetti\" title=\"Daniel D. Chetti\">Daniel D. Chetti</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/CBCNC\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"CBCNC\">CBCNC</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Board_of_Theological_Education_of_the_Senate_of_Serampore_College&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<dl><dt>Notes</dt></dl>\n<div class=\"reflist columns references-column-width\" style=\"-moz-column-width: 30em; -webkit-column-width: 30em; column-width: 30em; list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Wati Longchar <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external autonumber\" href=\"http://www.wcc-coe.org/wcc/what/education/mf101.pdf\">[1]</a> Towards a common strategy and mechanism</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Christian Conference of Asia <cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20081030053340/http://www.cca.org.hk/resources/papers/conference/ete20813p.htm\">\"Archived copy\"</a>. Archived from <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.cca.org.hk/resources/papers/conference/ete20813p.htm\">the original</a> on 30 October 2008<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">22 August</span> 2008</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Archived+copy&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.cca.org.hk%2Fresources%2Fpapers%2Fconference%2Fete20813p.htm&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABoard+of+Theological+Education+of+the+Senate+of+Serampore+College\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span> TOWARDS A COMMON STRATEGY AND MECHANISM TO FACILITATE \nTHEOLOGICAL EDUCATION AND HUMAN RESOURCE DEVELOPMENT \nIN SOUTH ASIA CHURCHES</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Under Section 2 (f) of the UGC Act, 1956, <i><b>University</b> means a University established or incorporated by or under a Central Act, a Provincial Act or a State Act, and includes any such institution as may, in consultation with the University concerned, be recoginsed by the Commission in accordance with the regulations made in this behalf under this Act.</i>  The UGC took the opinion that the Senate fell under the purview of Section 2 (f) of the said Act since <i>The Serampore College Act, 1918</i> was passed by the Government of West Bengal.<cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20080926195054/http://senateofseramporecollege.org/act/UGC.htm\">\"Archived copy\"</a>. Archived from <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.senateofseramporecollege.org/act/UGC.htm\">the original</a> on 26 September 2008<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">15 November</span> 2015</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Archived+copy&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.senateofseramporecollege.org%2Fact%2FUGC.htm&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABoard+of+Theological+Education+of+the+Senate+of+Serampore+College\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.ugc.ac.in/policy/ugcact1956.html\">The University Grants Commission Act, 1956</a> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20071229114428/http://www.ugc.ac.in/policy/ugcact1956.html\">Archived</a> 29 December 2007 at the <a href=\"/wiki/Wayback_Machine\" title=\"Wayback Machine\">Wayback Machine</a>.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-5\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a href=\"/wiki/Murli_Manohar_Joshi\" title=\"Murli Manohar Joshi\">Murli Manohar Joshi</a>, Higher Education in India Vision and Action, A paper presented at the UNESCO World Conference on Higher Education in the Twenty First Century, Paris, 5\u20139 October 1998. Internet, accessed 22 August 2008.  <cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20120223010953/http://education.nic.in/unhighedu.asp\">\"Archived copy\"</a>. Archived from <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://education.nic.in/unhighedu.asp\">the original</a> on 23 February 2012<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">15 November</span> 2015</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Archived+copy&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Feducation.nic.in%2Funhighedu.asp&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABoard+of+Theological+Education+of+the+Senate+of+Serampore+College\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display: